{
  "texts": [
    "Problem (P-CA) is a non-convex optimization problem in the LLM parameter space.",
    "We introduce the standard Lagrangian function (or Lagrangian) for Problem (P-CA):L(π θ, λ):= E x E y ∼ π θ r(x, y) + λ ⊤ h(x, y) -β D KL (π θ (• | x) ∥ π ref (• | x))(1)where we use notation λ:= [ λ 1,..., λ m] ⊤ and h:= [ h 1,..., h m] ⊤, and λ i ≥ 0 is the ith Lagrangian multiplier or dual variable.",
    "We also denote L(π θ, λ) by L p (π θ, λ) with the subscript p. The associated dual function is given by D p (λ):= maximize θ ∈ Θ L p (π θ, λ), where a Lagrangian maximizer is denoted by π ⋆ p (λ):= π θ ⋆ (λ).",
    "Thus, we introduce the dual problem for Problem (P-CA): minimizeλ ≥ 0 D p (λ)(2)and denote a dual minimizer by λ ⋆ p, i.e., D ⋆ p:= D p (λ ⋆ p).",
    "The dual function is generally nondifferentiable in non-convex optimization [3]."
  ]
}